{"title_page": "Cricket at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games \u2013 Men's twenty20 tournament", "text_new": "{{main|Cricket at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games}}\n{{Infobox cricket tournament\n| name = Men's Twenty20 tournament<br />at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| fromdate = 26 August 2017\n| todate = 29 August 2017\n| administrator = [[Southeast Asian Games Federation]]\n| cricket format = [[Twenty20]]\n| tournament format = [[Round-robin tournament|Round-robin]] and play-offs\n| host = [[Kinrara Academy Oval|Kinrara Oval]]<br />[[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]]\n| champions = {{cr|Singapore}}\n| count = \n| participants = 6\n| matches = 8\n| attendance = \n| player of the series = \n| most runs = {{flagicon|Singapore}} [[Navin Param]] (155)\n| most wickets = {{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Mohammad Shukri (cricketer)|Mohammad Shukri]] (10)\n| drs = \n| website = \n| previous_year = \n| previous_tournament = \n| next_year = \n| next_tournament = \n}}\n{{Cricket at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games}}\n\nThe '''men's Twenty20 [[cricket]]''' tournament at the [[2017 Southeast Asian Games]] will take place at [[Kinrara Academy Oval|Kinrara Oval]] in [[Selangor]] from 26 to 29 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kualalumpur2017.com.my/seagames-sport.cshtml?cid=32|title=KL 2017: Cricket|publisher=[[2017 Southeast Asian Games|KL 2017]]|accessdate=12 February 2017}}</ref> 6 teams will be split into 2 [[Round-robin tournament|round-robin]] groups. 1st placed teams in each group qualify for gold medal final while 2nd placed teams qualify for bronze medal final.\n\n==Competition schedule==\nThe following was the competition schedule for the men's Twenty20 competitions:\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:90%; line-height:1.25em;\"\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#FA7894\" align=center|RR||Round-robin\n|bgcolor=\"#7DE5FA\" align=center|B||3rd place play-off\n|bgcolor=\"#7DE5FA\" align=center|F||Final\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em au